7{padding-left:-3.9pt}.c8{margin-right:4.5pt}.title{padding-top:24pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:36pt;padding-bottom:6pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}.subtitle{padding-top:18pt;color:#666666;font-size:24pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Georgia";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;font-style:italic;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}li{color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:"Calibri"}p{margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:"Calibri"}h1{padding-top:24pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:24pt;padding-bottom:6pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h2{padding-top:18pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:18pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h3{padding-top:14pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:14pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h4{padding-top:12pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:12pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h5{padding-top:11pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:11pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h6{padding-top:10pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:10pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0791666666666666;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}</style></head><body class="c19 doc-content"><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c3">CONTRACT FOR USE OF THE SERVICE TERMS AND CONDITIONS </span></p><p class="c5 c11"><span class="c1 c3"></span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c0">This Contract (hereinafter &quot;</span><span class="c3">Contract</span><span class="c0">&quot;) regulates the relations emerging in connection with use of the mobile application or the website (hereinafter &quot;Service&quot;) operating under the brand name of &quot;International Child Development Center&quot; (hereinafter &quot; </span><span class="c3">Contractor</span><span class="c0">&quot;) by the user of the Service (hereinafter &quot;</span><span class="c3">Customer</span><span class="c1 c0">&quot;).</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">By registering on the mobile application or the website, the person is deemed a &quot;Customer&quot;. Through the Service, the Contractor uses the personal data that the User voluntarily enters into the Service to provide the following Services to the Customer through the Service and for further improvement of the operation of the Service. At the same time, by registering in the Service, the Customer is deemed to have voluntarily agreed to the collection and use of his personal data that entered by him/her into the Service, by the Contractor in the Service.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c0">By registering on the mobile application or the website and filling the necessary fields required on the mobile application or the website, the Customer wishes the </span><span class="c3">Participant</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;to use the Services provided by the Contractor and initiates this voluntarily and independently on his/her own.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer guarantees that this initiative of the Participant to use the Services provided by the Executive (registering in the Service, filling in the necessary fields in the Service, concluding a contract with the Contractor, etc.) is a joint decision made independently by the Customer and his/her spouse.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer knows and accepts in advance that the used to register on the mobile application or the website information (password, password, first name, last name, etc.) is independently determined by him and used and known only by him.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer guarantees that s/he will not share the information required to access his/her registered account (password, password, first name, last name, etc.) with others.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer confirms that the information entered in the fields required has been filled in by him/her personally by logging in through the account s/he has registered on the mobile application or the website.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer is personally, directly and fully responsible for the accuracy and reliability of that information.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">Terms used herein shall have the meaning set forth herein unless otherwise defined later.</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1 c0">The Contractor and the Customer may be referred to severally as &quot;Party&quot; and jointly as &quot;Parties&quot; in this Contract.</span></p><p class="c5 c11"><span class="c1 c0"></span></p><ol class="c4 lst-kix_list_3-0 start" start="1"><li class="c14 c15 c20 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1 c3">CONCEPTS</span></li></ol><p class="c11 c13"><span class="c1 c3"></span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Camp</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span class="c3">&ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is a place that includes the features and activities of a fun recreation center and an educational language course and teaches the language of the Customer&#39;s choice, organised in accordance with the legislation of the country of the camp and in the country that agreed between the Customer and the Contractor in advance.</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c1 c0">In addition to the classes in the language chosen by the Customer, various fun activities and competitions are held in the camp, as well as excursions to various sightseeing places of the country where the Camp is located;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">The language chosen by the Customer</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span class="c3">&ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is the one agreed between the Customer and the Contractor and is spoken in the camp and the lessons are held. This includes one of the choices between English, German, French, Spanish or Chinese.</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Services &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;Includes provision of a list of necessary documents provided by the Contractor to the Customer in regard with his/her child or children (Participant) required for the Participant&#39;s admission to the camp, moreover necessary advice and assistance regarding collection of those documents and application to the camp, accompanying the agreed Group with a Group leader to the camp;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Service fee &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is a fee paid for providing services and reserving a place in the Camp;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Order &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is an official request made by the Customer for the Participant to participate in the Camp;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Participant &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is one or more children of the Customer, agreed with the Contractor and planned to go to the Camp;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Various foreign countries &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is the country where the Camp is located, agreed with the Contractor;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Language course &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is a language course organized in the country where the Camp is located, agreed with the Contractor, and where the language chosen by the Customer is taught using effective and fun methods;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Intermediate level &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is the ability to speak and understand what is spoken at the level required for performing household chores and activities in the language of the Customer&#39;s choice;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Camp management &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is the management of the organization organizing the Camp to be held in the country agreed with the Contractor;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Agreed group &ndash; </span><span class="c1 c0">a group of several Participants and a Group leader gathered for the purpose of participating in the Camp agreed with the Contractor;</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">Group leader &ndash;</span><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;is an authorized representative of the Contractor who leads and supervises the Agreed group that will participate in the Camp agreed with the Contractor;</span></p><p class="c7 c11"><span class="c1 c0"></span></p><p class="c18"><span class="c1 c3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;WHEREAS:</span></p><ol class="c4 lst-kix_list_4-0 start" start="1"><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer guarantees that the Participant is mentally, spiritually and psychologically quite healthy;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer guarantees that the Participant can fully control his actions, inaction and fully understand his/her responsibility for their consequences;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer guarantees that the Participant can feel and behave completely freely in various foreign countries outside the control of the Customer;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c0 c1">The Customer guarantees that the Participant can understand and speak at an intermediate level in the language chosen by the Customer;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Contractor does not provide any services to the Customer regarding obtaining a visa to go to various foreign countries. However, if required, appropriate advice can be granted on how to apply to a suitable partner company for this purpose. In any case, the Contractor does not bear any responsibility for the expenses required and services of the partner company.</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">If any changes occur later in the information or documents provided by the Customer to the Contractor, the Customer must immediately inform the Contractor about it and submit the new information or documents to the Contractor;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Participant must go to the Camp only at the agreed time within the Agreed group agreed between the Customer and the Contractor and must return to the Republic of Azerbaijan at the agreed time within the Agreed group;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Customer guarantees that the Participant must unconditionally and immediately follow all the instructions of the Group leader appointed by the Contractor from the moment s/he boards the plane to fly out of the Republic of Azerbaijan until s/he returns to the Republic of Azerbaijan;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">Rules of conduct, ethical norms, rights and obligations in the Camp are determined and implemented by the legislation of the country where the Camp is located;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Participant must pass the &quot;Professional Compulsory Psychological Test&quot; provided by the Contractor. If the result of the test is satisfactory, the Participant will be considered psychologically tested and approved to go to the Camp. Otherwise, the Participant will not be allowed to go to the Camp;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">A total of 15 hours of lessons will be held in the Camp, with a minimum of 20 lessons per week. Customer can increase the number of lessons and hours by making extra payment.</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">Except for Budapest and the Czech Republic (in which it is required to successfully pass the English language test in order to receive a certificate at the end), in other European countries, America, Canada, the Republic of South Africa and the United Arab Emirates (Dubai), Participants will be given an accredited certificate by Feltom (by Cambridge). In Budapest and the Czech Republic, participants are not given a certificate;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">Girls and boys will be accommodated separately from each other in the Camp;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">The Contractor will assist to relatives or siblings to share the same room in the Camp;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">An additional payment of 100 Euros per week shall be made for the provision of halal food;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">Free laundry service is available at the Camp for Participants;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">Additional payment may be charged for Wi-Fi service;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">Classes and activities offered at the Camp (nature, museum and other trips, fun activities) are free for the Participants;</span></li><li class="c5 c10"><span class="c1 c0">Payments that are not included in the Service fee and are made additionally at the Camp at the Participant&#39;s own choice must be made in the currency of the country where the Camp locates;</span></li><li class="c16 li-bullet-1"><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp;Registration on the website of the Contractor is free;</span></li></ol><p class="c14 c11 c15"><span class="c1 c3"></span></p><p class="c14"><span class="c1 c3">&nbsp; &nbsp; THE PARTIES AGREED AS THE FOLLOWINGS:</span></p><p class="c18"><span class="c1 c0">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span></p><ol class="c4 lst-kix_list_5-3 start" start="1"><li class="c14 c15 c17 li-bullet-2"><span class="c1 c3">SUBJECT OF THE CONTRACT</span></li></ol><p class="c7 c11"><span class="c1 c0"></span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c0">The Con